Curator's comments: A piece of Assyrian war booty from Egypt; other Egyptian objects have been found at Nebi Yunus during subsequent Iraqi excavations.
Bibliographic references: Alexander 1928a / Baghdad in bygone days (p.286, illustration opposite)
Acquisition notes: Found at Nebi Yunus by Claudius James Rich who described it as "this curious little stone chair" (reference given in C.M. Alexander, 'Baghdad in bygone days', p. 286).
Additional IDs: Miscellaneous number: BS.428 (Egyptian Saloon slip number)
